.head 3 +  Function: AvailabilityOk
.head 4 -  Description: To compare the passed in ordered amount of the passed in stock Item
against the total availability of the stock item in the stock_item_Sale
file.  If availability Ok, ie: total availability - ordered amount isnt less 
than the threshold (20 or so) then it returns true else false
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Boolean:
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Number: nItemNo
.head 5 -  Number: nYear
.head 5 -  Number: nOrderedAmount
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Sql Handle: hSqlHandle
.head 5 -  Boolean: bSqlHandle
.head 5 -  String: sSql
.head 5 -  Number: nInd
.head 5 -  Number: nAvailThreshold
.head 5 -  Number: nTotalAvail
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Set bSqlHandle = SqlConnect( hSqlHandle ) 
.head 5 +  If bSqlHandle
.head 6 -  Call SqlSetLockTimeout( hSqlHandle, SQLTIMEOUT )
.head 5 +  Else
.head 6 -  Call SalMessageBox( 'Connection in Database Error, could not obtain handle!', 'Error', MB_Ok )
.head 6 -  Return FALSE
.head 5 -  ! INSTEAD OF CHECKING THE MIMINUM OF 20 - WE NOW NEED TO DO SOME
SPECIAL PROCESSING IF THE TOTAL AVAILABLE IS LESS THAN 0.
INSTEAD OF JUST PRINTING THE MESSAGE OF SUBJECT TO LIFTING EG THE 
STOCK COUNT MESSAGE(I THINK), WE NEED TO FETCH ALL CUSTOMERS WHO
HAVE ORDERED THIS STOCK ITEM BY ORDER DATE AND THEN WORK DOWN
FROM THE GROWING COUNT MINUS EACH PERSONS ORDER AMT UNTIL WE 
HIT THE CUSTOMER THAT WE ARE CURRENTLY DOING AN ACKNOWLEDGEMENT
FOR - IF HIS ORDER HASNT SENT THE TOTAL AVAIL(DYNAMICALLY BEING CALCULATED
DOWN BELOW ZERO THEN HE GETS THE OK MESSAGE - IF IT IS NEGATIVE EG WHEN
HE ORDERED THAT STOCK ITEM WAS ALREADY AT  -100 THEN HE HAS TO
GET THE MESSAGE THAT ITS SUBJECT TO LIFTING   
.head 5 -  ! Change this figure if we need to change the minimum availability before 
printing the Ack_Count_message.
.head 5 -  Set nAvailThreshold = 20
.head 5 -  Set nTotalAvail = 0
.head 5 -  Set sSql = 'SELECT Tot_Avail FROM Stock_Item_Sale INTO :nTotalAvail
WHERE Stock_Item_No = :nItemNo AND Year_Of_Sale = :nYear'
.head 5 +  If SqlPrepare( hSqlHandle, sSql )
.head 6 +  If SqlExecute( hSqlHandle )
.head 7 -  Call SqlFetchNext( hSqlHandle, nInd )
.head 6 +  Else
.head 7 -  Call SalMessageBox( 'SqlExecute had a error in function AvailabilityOk.  Please contact programmers.', 'Error', MB_Ok )
.head 7 +  If bSqlHandle
.head 8 -  Call SqlDisconnect( hSqlHandle )
.head 7 -  Return FALSE
.head 5 +  Else
.head 6 -  Call SalMessageBox( 'SqlPrepare had a error in function AvailabilityOk.  Please contact programmers.', 'Error', MB_Ok )
.head 6 +  If bSqlHandle
.head 7 -  Call SqlDisconnect( hSqlHandle )
.head 6 -  Return FALSE
.head 5 -  ! THE FOLLOWING CHECK IS WRONG ANYWAY - THE TOTAL AVAILABLE FOR
A STOCK ITEM ALREADY HAS THE ORDERED AMOUNT TAKEN OFF IT FOR THE
CUSTOMER - WHAT YOU ARE DOING HERE IS CHECKING AGAIN BY TAKING
THE AMOUNT OFF AGAIN - YOU ONLY NEED TO CHECK IF THE TOTAL AVAILABLE
IS GREATER THAN ZERO - IF IT IS - WE HAVE THE STOCK AVAILABLE FOR THE
CUSTOMER
.head 5 +  If nTotalAvail - nOrderedAmount < nAvailThreshold
.head 6 +  If bSqlHandle
.head 7 -  Call SqlDisconnect( hSqlHandle )
.head 6 -  Return FALSE
.head 5 +  Else
.head 6 +  If bSqlHandle
.head 7 -  Call SqlDisconnect( hSqlHandle )
.head 6 -  Return TRUE
